    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### Investigate\r\n\r\nLeolin noticed that the <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-boombox\" style=\"color: #58BEF9; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Bass </span> track didn't line up with the other tracks, and it was missing a <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-drum\" style=\"color: #E565F5; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Beat </span> track. She wondered if we could add those in so everything played at the same time to create **harmony**:\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/5e899e3e7955fc07306fd942367df0a3-image-1743110245361.png)\r\n\r\nTry to recreate the code above on your own, or follow the step-by-step instructions below:\r\n\r\n1) Move the <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-boombox\" style=\"color: #58BEF9; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Bass </span> track into the <code style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 148, 202); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play together</code> block [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=id:bass_block---id-up-inside:play_sounds_together).\r\n2) Drag out a new <code style=\"background-color: rgb(116, 53, 178); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play</code> block into the <code style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 148, 202); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play together</code> block [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=flyout-id:play_toolbox---id-up-inside:play_sounds_together).\r\n3) Set the track to a <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-drum\" style=\"color: #E565F5; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Beat </span>.\r\n\r\n> If you're stuck, try clicking the <i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i> icons for hints!\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-pencil\"></i> **Harmony:** When different notes or sounds play together to support a melody and make the music sound fuller ",
